    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a narrative journey through time, divided into four chronological sections: "The Grunge Explosion," "The Post-Grunge Polish," "The Emo & Metalcore Ascension," and "The Mainstream Decline." This thematic, timeline-based structure was chosen to guide the user through the evolution of these interconnected genres logically. The top navigation allows users to jump between eras, while interactive elements within each section—such as a timeline chart, genre characteristic comparisons, and clickable "Key Band" cards—encourage exploration and deeper understanding. The user flow is designed to be both linear for a story-like experience and non-linear for users who want to explore specific topics, making the complex history digestible and engaging. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        1.  **Timeline Chart (Chart.js):** Report Info -> Genre Popularity Over Time. Goal -> Show change. Viz -> Line Chart. Interaction -> Hover to see dominant genres for a specific year. Justification -> A line chart is the most effective way to visualize the rise and fall of genres over a continuous period. Library -> Chart.js.
        2.  **Genre Comparison (HTML/Tailwind):** Report Info -> Sonic and lyrical characteristics of each genre. Goal -> Compare. Viz -> Tabbed content cards. Interaction -> Clicking tabs reveals details for each genre. Justification -> Tabs provide a clean, space-efficient way to compare distinct sets of information side-by-side. Method -> HTML/CSS.
        3.  **Key Band Cards (HTML/Tailwind):** Report Info -> Influential bands for each era. Goal -> Inform. Viz -> Grid of interactive cards. Interaction -> Hovering on a card reveals a brief description of the band's impact. Justification -> Cards are a visually appealing way to present key figures, and the hover interaction encourages user engagement without cluttering the UI. Method -> HTML/CSS/JS.
        4.  **Textual Analysis (HTML/Tailwind):** Report Info -> Detailed explanations of the rise and fall of each movement. Goal -> Inform. Viz -> Accordion sections. Interaction -> Clicking to expand/collapse detailed text. Justification -> Accordions keep the layout clean and allow users to opt-in to reading longer-form content, preventing information overload. Method -> HTML/CSS/JS.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
